Libraries will now be open on Saturdays from 1 pm until 5 pm and Sundays from 1 to 5 pm. JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg has extended the operating hours of city libraries in a bid to increase access to a safe studying environment, especially for disadvantaged young people.On Tuesday, Mayor Herman Mashaba launched the pilot project at the Jabavu Library in Soweto.Libraries will now be open on Saturdays from 1 pm until 5 pm.Mashaba's spokesperson Tony Taverna-Turison said: This decision originates from the mayor s State of the City Address earlier this year where we announced that we will be piloting the extension of the opening hours of a number of city libraries. There will be operating libraries from Monday to Friday 9 am to 8 pm and Sundays from 1 to 5 pm. Sandton, Orange Farm, Ennerdale, Yeoville and Diepsloot libraries will also extend their hours.Please read to get more information on the Extended Operating Hours at libraries initiative #MashabaInAction pic.twitter.com/U6MfGsgknS